<topic id="topic-1">
   <title>MathType for OxygenXML - DITA1.3</title>
   <body>
        <p>In elementary algebra, the <b>quadratic formula</b> is the solution of the quadratic equation.</p>
        <mathml>
            <m:math
                xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
                <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:mfrac>
                    <m:mrow>
                        <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                        <m:mi>b</m:mi>
                        <m:mo>&#xB1;</m:mo>
                        <m:msqrt>
                            <m:msup>
                                <m:mi>b</m:mi>
                                <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                            </m:msup>
                            <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                            <m:mn>4</m:mn>
                            <m:mi>a</m:mi>
                            <m:mi>c</m:mi>
                        </m:msqrt>
                    </m:mrow>
                    <m:mrow>
                        <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                        <m:mi>a</m:mi>
                    </m:mrow>
                </m:mfrac>
            </m:math>
        </mathml>

        <p><b>Water is made from two molecules</b> - Hydrogen and Oxygen. If you put the two gasses together, along with energy, you can make water.</p>
        <mathml>
            <m:math class="wrs_chemistry"
                xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
                <m:msub>
                    <m:mi mathvariant="normal">H</m:mi>
                    <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                </m:msub>
                <m:mfenced>
                    <m:mi mathvariant="normal">g</m:mi>
                </m:mfenced>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                <m:msub>
                    <m:mi mathvariant="normal">O</m:mi>
                    <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                </m:msub>
                <m:mfenced>
                    <m:mi mathvariant="normal">g</m:mi>
                </m:mfenced>
                <m:mo>&#x21CC;</m:mo>
                <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                <m:msub>
                    <m:mi mathvariant="normal">H</m:mi>
                    <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                </m:msub>
                <m:mi mathvariant="normal">O</m:mi>
                <m:mfenced>
                    <m:mi mathvariant="normal">l</m:mi>
                </m:mfenced>
            </m:math>
        </mathml>

